<TITLE> <font size=1 color=black>BDR trial</font><br>Trial of hospital unit mutineers begins </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 28 (bdnews24.com)  A special BDR court in Dhaka on Wednesday began trying 256 border guards of the hospital unit, accused of Feb 25-26, 2009 mutiny. The special court-6, set up at the Darbar Hall at the paramilitary force's Pelkhana headquarters, convened at around 9:30am with complainant Nayek Subeder Nannu Miah, a medical assistant, naming the accused. Outgoing Bangladesh Rifles director general Maj Gen Mainul Islam, who heads the panel of judges, adjourned the court until Thursday. Among the total accused, 90 are currently in jail while the remaining 166 were on duty at the hospital. Gen Islam ordered that all the remaining accused be arrested and produced before the court the next day. Quoting the witnesses prosecutor Lt Col SMA Al Muyid in his statement said that four doctors were killed during the mutiny. Female doctors were not even spared from torture, he said. Gen Islam became emotional while the prosecutor was describing the events; he wiped tears several times and said sorry for being emotional. The court ended at around 11:30am. 
